	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Please, don't post unless you actually know the game, and have aquired some knowledge. Until you do that, you're simply making yourself look a fool...<BR>
All i'm seeing is a bunch of lvl 10-30 noobie shamans/necros/wizards screaming 'no! my class is better! waaaah!'<BR>
But no worries, maybe your balls will drop one day - and you may understand.<BR>
<BR>
Wizards are mostly group oriented, they have some quad kiting skills - But they are not highly efficient or skilled at soloing. They are built to do serious damage in a group... That's what they do, that's what they are.<BR>
<BR>
Necros are mostly solo throughout their career, they have great bulk soloing skills, with little downtime, and they take few hits due to their snare/fear combo. However, if they try to solo any post-50 mob, they are instantly summoned and killed. Soloing is what they do best, to take down low-blues fast and get great exp from doing it. Though they can do good damage in a group, and even mana dump. That's what they do, that's what they are...<BR>
<BR>
Shamans are a a kind of halfway house. They are good in groups, particularly for slowing mobs. They can solo, though not as efficiently as necro's at lower levels. However, at later levels they can kill mobs that no other can. I've seen lvl 60 shamans solo phase spiders and dragon constructs in Dragon Necropolis, solo arena mobs in Kael, and even once saw a lvl 60 shaman solo one of the weaker dragons in Western Wastes. That's what they do, that's what they are...<BR>
<BR>
As for whatever class is the best, it doesn't matter, they all do different things. Necro's solo better, faster and more efficiently earlier on. But simply can't take the mobs Shamans can later on in the game. Whereas wizzies can outdamage the other two easily in a group setting. It's all down to personal choice.<BR>
<BR>
To those posting decent info, nice one. To those ones screaming that their class is better, /rude. You know who you are, o pubeless ones. :)<BR>
<BR>
Somnus<BR>
Revenant of the Gate<BR>
Quellious<BR>
<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
